[[File:8th_Division_Brigadier.jpg|thumb|Alliance [[8th Division]] Brigadier]]
'''Brigadier''' was a [[Military rank/Legends|rank]] in some military organizations, senior to a [[Colonel/Legends|Colonel]] but below a [[Major General]]. Officers with the rank of Brigadier did not necessarily command [[Brigade/Legends|Brigades]], but brigade commanders could have been referred to as "brigadiers," even if they held a different rank. [[Brigadier General/Legends|Brigadier General]] was also a military rank.

==History==
The earliest direct evidence for the rank of Brigadier dates from around the time of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], when it was borne by officers like [[Locus Geen]], who led ground forces during the [[Coruscant Insurrection]], and [[Gideon Tarkin]], a member of a military family from [[Eriadu/Legends|Eriadu]] whose brother [[Wilhuff Tarkin/Legends|Wilhuff]] later became the feared [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Grand Moff/Legends|Grand Moff]] of the [[Outland Regions]]. Little is known of the exact significance of the rank of Brigadier at this time, but it seems that it was confined to the non-[[Cloning/Legends|clone]] units which came to augment the original [[Grand Army of the Republic/Legends|Grand Army of the Republic]] over the course of the war, and Brigadier Tarkin was recorded as already holding his rank on his homeworld shortly before the [[Military Creation Act/Legends|Military Creation Act]], making it probable (though not quite certain) that a rank of Brigadier was already in use with locally-based military forces within Republic space before the outbreak of the war.

Under the Empire, there were very few references to a rank of Brigadier, with the position of [[High Colonel/Legends|High Colonel]] being somewhat analogous. However, there was at least one individual who held this title, Brigadier [[Nevar/Legends|Nevar]], who was aboard the [[All Terrain Armored Transport/Legends|AT-AT]] walker ''[[Blizzard 2/Legends|Blizzard 2]]'' at the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]], and was apparently assassinated shortly before it was destroyed by the [[Snowspeeder/Legends|snowspeeders]] of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]].

In the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]], the rank of Brigadier was used within the military-style rank hierarchy of [[New Republic Intelligence Service|New Republic Intelligence]], even though NRI was not known to have contained units designated as Brigades, or indeed to have had any higher hierarchy of general ranks. Brigadiers in Intelligence included [[Collomus]], [[Colin Darkmere]], and former front-line soldier [[Bren Derlin/Legends|Bren Derlin]].

==Behind the scenes==
In the real world, "Brigadier" and "Brigadier General" are equivalent ranks in the British and American armed forces.

Brigadier [[Locus Geen]] is called a "General" in [[The Dark Forces Saga]] online game scenario, [http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=starwars/article/sw20050407a] and the Imperial officer identified as "Brig. Nevar" in the book ''[[Inside the Worlds of Star Wars Trilogy]]''&mdash;apparently the only reference to a "Brigadier" in the Imperial military&mdash;had originally been named as "General Nevar" in the [[Star Wars Customizable Card Game]].

